'''Alireza Rahimi''' ({{lang-fa|علیرضا رحیمی}}) (born March 1, 1955) is the current President of the [[Islamic Republic of Iran Handball Federation]] since 2017. He was previously president of three sport clubs including: [[Persepolis Athletic and Cultural Club]],<ref>http://fc-perspolis.com/news_content/main/newsId:21288</ref> [[Sepahan F.C.]]<ref>[http://www.farsnews.com/newstext.php?nn=9005183007 خبرگزاری فارس]</ref> based in [[Isfahan]], [[Iran]] and [[Rah Ahan F.C.|Rah Ahan FC]]. He was a board member of the [[Islamic Republic of Iran Football Federation]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hamshahrionline.ir/news-162715.aspx |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-04-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120307235042/http://www.hamshahrionline.ir/news-162715.aspx |archive-date=2012-03-07 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> and also was the chairman of [[Islamic Republic of Iran Handball Federation]],<ref>[http://isna.ir/fa/news/8812-13969/-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%B6%D8%A7-%D8%B1%D8%AD%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D9%81%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%87%D9%86%D8%AF%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%81%D8%A7 خبرگزاری ایسنا]</ref> from 1994 to 2010. He is also a former player of [[Sepahan]].

